pulfalight.title: Labels for description notes should display for collection records

comments.body: Do you mean the header/label would read "Scope and Contents" as opposed to "Description," which is what currently displays?
@faithc Yes
I think that should be ok. Thanks.

I'm still not sure I totally get the logic behind it. You're saying that any scopecontent note currently gets a "description" header applied to it. Would it be too complicated to say to use "description" unless the "content warning" label exists? I don't think it's a huge deal either way. I just want to make sure I understand how these headers are currently being applied. Thanks.

> I'm still not sure I totally get the logic behind it. You're saying that any scopecontent note currently gets a "description" header applied to it. Would it be too complicated to say to use "description" unless the "content warning" label exists? I don't think it's a huge deal either way. I just want to make sure I understand how these headers are currently being applied. Thanks.

In components we're taking the header that's in ASpace always, for collections we're not splitting out headers at all - all scopecontent notes are getting the "Description" header. I'm saying it would be easy to make collections take the headers always, but then it'll say whatever the header is in ASpace instead - in this case, "Scope & Contents" instead of "Description"
Ah ok, gotcha. Thanks!
